(1. Scope) Tj
72 624 Td
(This document specifies all electrical, mechanical, and software interfaces of the NOVA BMS.) Tj
72 610 Td
(All interface requirements are derived from and traceable to NOVA-SRS-001.) Tj
72 596 Td
() Tj
72 582 Td
(2. CAN Bus Interface) Tj
72 568 Td
(VX-IRS-C001: BMS shall connect to vehicle CAN-H/CAN-L via 120-ohm termination resistor.) Tj
72 554 Td
(VX-IRS-C002: CAN baud rate: 500 kbps \(nominal\), switchable to 250 kbps for diagnostics.) Tj
72 540 Td
(VX-IRS-C003: CAN message 0x1A0 - SOC Broadcast.) Tj
72 526 Td
(  Byte 0-1: SOC value \(0-1000, resolution 0.1%\).) Tj
72 512 Td
(  Byte 2-3: Pack voltage \(0-65535, resolution 0.01 V\).) Tj
72 498 Td
(  Byte 4: Pack temperature \(0-255, offset -40, resolution 1 degree C\).) Tj
72 484 Td
(  Byte 5: Status flags \(bit 0: charging, bit 1: fault, bit 2: balancing\).) Tj
72 470 Td
(  Cycle time: 100 ms. See HAG-REQ-F004 in NOVA-SRS-001.) Tj
72 456 Td
(VX-IRS-C004: CAN message 0x1A1 - Cell Voltage Detailed.) Tj
ET

endstream
